    <li><a href="#urls">URL Reference</a></li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2 id="submitting">1. Submitting a Ticket</h2>
<p>Any visitor (including guests) can submit a support ticket at <a href="/HelpDesk/ticket/new">/HelpDesk/ticket/new</a>.</p>
<ol>
    <li>Fill in <strong>Subject</strong> and <strong>Description</strong>.</li>
    <li>Provide your name and email address.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong>. A unique ticket number is assigned (e.g. <code>TK-00042</code>).</li>
    <li>Site admins are notified by email immediately.</li>
    <li>Track your ticket at <a href="/HelpDesk/ticket/status">/HelpDesk/ticket/status</a> using your ticket number and email.</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2 id="ticket-lifecycle">2. Ticket Lifecycle</h2>
<table class="doc-table">
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Status</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Who sets it</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>open</strong></td><td>Awaiting staff response</td><td>System (on submit or customer reply)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>on_hold</strong></td><td>Waiting on customer or third party</td><td>Staff</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>resolved</strong></td><td>Staff has provided a resolution; awaiting customer confirmation</td><td>Staff</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>closed</strong></td><td>Complete. Auto-closed after 14 days in resolved if no reply.</td><td>System or Staff</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<p>
When a ticket is moved to <strong>resolved</strong> or <strong>closed</strong> by staff, the customer receives an email with
a direct link to view the ticket. The email explains that they can reply to reopen if the issue persists.
</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="admin-views">3. Admin Ticket Views</h2>
<p>Staff with admin access see the HelpDesk admin panel at <a href="/HelpDesk/admin">/HelpDesk/admin</a>.</p>
<table class="doc-table">
    <thead><tr><th>URL</th><th>Shows</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>/HelpDesk/admin/tickets</code></td><td>All tickets (default view)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/HelpDesk/admin/tickets/open</code></td><td>Open tickets only</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/HelpDesk/admin/tickets/resolved</code></td><td>Resolved — awaiting auto-close</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/HelpDesk/admin/tickets/closed</code></td><td>Closed tickets</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/HelpDesk/admin/tickets_alert</code></td><td>Count of open tickets (used by Daily Plan)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<p>Click a ticket number to view the full conversation thread and take actions.</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="status-management">4. Managing Ticket Status</h2>
<p>From the ticket view page (<code>/HelpDesk/ticket/view/&lt;ticket_number&gt;</code>), staff can:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Select a new status from the <strong>Update Status</strong> dropdown.</li>
    <li>Optionally add a <strong>Resolution Note</strong> — this is recorded in the ticket thread as an audit message.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Update</strong>. The change is logged and the customer is notified by email if the status moves to resolved or closed.</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2 id="reminders">5. Sending a Reminder</h2>
<p>
If a customer has not responded to an on_hold ticket, staff can send a reminder email
from the ticket view page by clicking <strong>Send Reminder</strong>.
This sends an email to the customer referencing the open ticket number and a link to view it.
</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="auto-close">6. Auto-Close of Stale Tickets</h2>
<p>
When the admin ticket list is loaded, the system checks for any <em>resolved</em> tickets
that have not had an update in <strong>14 or more days</strong>.
Those tickets are automatically moved to <em>closed</em> and a system message is added to the thread recording the auto-close date.
No manual action is required — this prevents resolved queues from growing indefinitely.
</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="reopen">7. Customer Reply Reopens a Ticket</h2>
<p>
If a customer sends a reply on a ticket that is in <em>resolved</em> or <em>closed</em> status,
the system automatically resets the status back to <em>open</em>. A status-change message is added to the thread.
Staff are notified by email of the reopen.
This means customers never need to file a new ticket if their original issue returns.
</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="notifications">8. Email Notifications</h2>
<p>Email notifications are sent to all site admins in the following events:</p>
<ul>
    <li>New ticket submitted</li>
    <li>Customer reply posted</li>
    <li>Staff reply posted</li>
</ul>
<p>Customers receive email when:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Ticket moved to <em>resolved</em> or <em>closed</em> (includes link to view/reopen)</li>
    <li>Staff sends a reminder</li>
</ul>
<p>Email uses <code>Comserv::Util::EmailNotification</code>. Ensure the site's outgoing mail configuration is correct for notifications to work.</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="daily-plan">9. HelpDesk in the Daily Plan</h2>
<p>
The Daily Plan (<a href="/planning/daily">/planning/daily</a>) includes a collapsible <strong>HelpDesk Panel</strong>
showing the count and summary of open support tickets. It is loaded from the
<code>/HelpDesk/admin/tickets_alert</code> endpoint.
</p>
<p>
The <strong>Start Day</strong> action also queries HelpDesk ticket counts as part of the AI-assisted morning briefing,
so open tickets surface in the daily priorities even without manually opening the HelpDesk panel.
</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="site-scoping">10. Site Scoping (Multi-Site)</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Tickets belong to the site they were submitted on (<code>site_name</code> field).</li>
    <li>Site admins only see tickets from their own site.</li>
    <li><strong>CSC admins</strong> see tickets across all sites — allowing central support management.</li>
    <li>The <code>tickets_alert</code> endpoint and Daily Plan panel respect the same site-scoping rules.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

